/* Remove rounding from ALL Kendo utility rounded classes */
.k-rounded-sm,
.k-rounded-md,
.k-rounded-lg,
.k-rounded-full {
    border-radius: 0 !important;
}

/* Specifically target Grid toolbar button */
.k-grid .k-toolbar .k-button {
    border-radius: 0 !important;
    background: white !important;
    color: black !important;
    border: 1px solid black !important;
    box-shadow: none !important;
}

/* Remove theme “solid” styling */
.k-grid .k-toolbar .k-button.k-button-solid {
    background: white !important;
    border: 1px solid black !important;
    color: black !important;
}

/* Hover */
.k-grid .k-toolbar .k-button:hover {
    background: #f2f2f2 !important;
}
🔎 Why Previous CSS Didn’t Work

New Telerik themes (v5+) use utility classes like:

k-rounded-md
k-button-solid-base
k-button-md

Those apply border-radius AFTER .k-button, so unless you override .k-rounded-*, rounding stays.

🧠 Best Practice (Cleaner Way)

If you want your whole app permanently flat, add this once globally:

:root {
    --kendo-border-radius-sm: 0px;
    --kendo-border-radius-md: 0px;
    --kendo-border-radius-lg: 0px;
}

This overrides theme variables instead of fighting CSS everywhere.

